@database "Extention.guide"
@width 80
@node main "Extention List Contents"

       @{b} Amiga Guide Extention Lister

       By Robbie Wegner. V1.7@{ub}

    Click here to @{"Search" system "run s:ExtListersearch Sample3.Guide.3 "} for string.

 List of @{" Amiga Guides " link " .Guide 10000"} @{" Documents " link " .Doc 10010"} @{" ReadMe's " link " .readme 10020"} @{" .txt " link " .txt 10030"}  @{"DirAll" link "All 0"} SYS:Documents/

 List of @{" Amiga Guides " link " .Guide 10001"} @{" Documents " link " .Doc 10011"} @{" ReadMe's " link " .readme 10021"} @{" .txt " link " .txt 10031"}  @{"DirAll" link "All 1"} SYS:System/

 List of @{" Amiga Guides " link " .Guide 10002"} @{" Documents " link " .Doc 10012"} @{" ReadMe's " link " .readme 10022"} @{" .txt " link " .txt 10032"}  @{"DirAll" link "All 2"} SYS:Tools/


 @{b}List of@{ub} @{" Amiga Guides " link " .Guide 3 all"} @{" Documents " link " .Doc 3 all"} @{" ReadMe's " link " .readme 3 all"} @{" .txt " link " .txt 3 all"}  @{b}ExtALL.@{ub}

 @{b}List of@{ub} @{"THE WORKS!" link "Theworks"}

 INFO-
   This is a "Same extentions across all directory selections" sample Guide
 generated by the ExtLister script.

 It has the "Directory ALL", "Extention ALL" and "THE WORKS!" list options
 switched on. You can switch all of these off, or have them in any
 combination.
   The "Customised Button names" option is switched on as well for all except
 the ".Txt" button. If you do not specify this option or don't give a button
 a name as is the case here, the script will give it the extention by default.

   "Documents" would become ".Doc" for instance, "Amiga Guides" would be
 ".Guides" etc.
 
   The "Amiga Guides" have the "Extra Tool Button" switched off. Normally
 I would have these "Extra tool Buttons" all on and the same name for each to
 make the lists look a bit neater in the "THE WORKS!" and "Directory ALL" if
 they have been switched on! I have given them different names here and
 switched one off just to show that they can.

 Some buttons are set to DMCR, If you have the S: scripts installed, try
 clicking on one of these buttons. The Floating tool bar should appear.
 See installation in the documentation to see how it works!  

  The Sort option has been left off for the main ReadMe lists. They are sorted
 by directory as read off the disk, rather than by file name. All the others
 are sorted by file. (The Extention ALL "Readme" list is sorted however.)

 NOTE: The search function will not work until the ExtListerSearch file is put
 in the S: directory and AskEnv is put in the C: directory.

  You cannot load the actual files listed, cos they are on my machine :^) 
@endnode
